description._content: Image Description from historic lecture booklet: "The Consumers' Wholesale Society with head-quarters in Copenhagen was established in 1896. The first local cooperative buying association was formed in 1866. The annual turnover of this organization is now about $41,000,000. About one fourth of their goods is manufactured in their own stores. It sells only to members."
